<refsection condition="ref.description">
<title>Description</title><para>A <tag>titleabbrev</tag> holds an abbreviated version of a
      <tag>title</tag>. One common use of
      <tag>titleabbrev</tag> is for the text used in running headers
      or footers, when the proper title is too long to be used
      conveniently.</para>

      <refsection><info><title>Processing expectations</title></info>
        

        <para>May be formatted inline or as a displayed block, depending on
        context. Abbreviated titles are usually used only in specific
        contexts, such as headers and footers, and are suppressed everywhere
        else.</para>
</refsection>

